==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hebrew
<hw>He"brew</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>H⟦eacute⟧breu</ets>, L. <ets>Hebraeus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. Heb.
<ets>'ibhr⟦imac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An appellative of
Abraham or of one of his descendants, esp. in the line of Jacob; an
Israelite; a Jew.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There came one that had escaped and told Abram the
<qex>Hebrew</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Gen. xiv. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The language of the Hebrews; -- one of the Semitic
family of languages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebrew</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hebrew
<hw>He"brew</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the Hebrews;
<as>as, the <ex>Hebrew</ex> language or rites</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hebrew calendar</ent>⟦br⟧
